agent-tts licensing
===================

The agent-tts source code is dual-licensed under your choice of:

  - MIT License (see LICENSE-MIT)
  - Apache License, Version 2.0 (see LICENSE-APACHE)

SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT OR Apache-2.0

This applies to all source files in `src/` UNLESS a different SPDX header
appears at the top of the file. The two exceptions are:

  - `src/piper.zig`            — SPDX: GPL-3.0-or-later (links libpiper)
  - `vendor/piper1-gpl/`       — upstream GPL-3.0-or-later (not redistributed)
  - `vendor/zaudio/`           — upstream MIT
  - `vendor/zaudio/libs/miniaudio` — upstream public domain (Unlicense)

GPL contamination
-----------------

libpiper (https://github.com/OHF-Voice/piper1-gpl) is GPL-3.0-or-later.
When agent-tts is built with `-Dwith-piper=true` and distributed as a binary,
the combined work derives from libpiper and is therefore covered by GPL-3.0.

Concretely:

  - Source code distribution: MIT OR Apache-2.0 (always).
  - Binary distribution without piper (`-Dwith-piper=false`, the default):
    MIT OR Apache-2.0.
  - Binary distribution with piper linked: GPL-3.0-or-later.

If you want to use agent-tts in a closed-source / non-GPL product, build
without piper and only use the `say` engine (`--engine say`).

Voice models
------------

The Pt-BR Faber voice (`pt_BR-faber-medium.onnx`) is downloaded from
https://github.com/rhasspy/piper-voices at runtime and carries its own
license (typically CC-BY-NC). agent-tts does not redistribute the voice model.

Trademarks
----------

"Piper" and "ONNX Runtime" are properties of their respective owners.
This project is not affiliated with them.
